{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c595731-6d64-469d-9ca0-039cd168f1a6","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" in results with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e733be8c-a724-4919-ad0f-c839061ef046","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look anything up or use tools.\n\nHere's the information:\n\n**MSTest**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n\n**xUnit**: `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]`\n\n**NUnit**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n\n**TUnit**: `[Skip(\"reason\")]`\n\nI can answer this directly without tools.","outputTokens":419,"requestId":"BC21:22ED17:24E177:2B0A1A:69FA9399"},"id":"bc67d53f-f539-471c-b517-81ffa3bbe83b","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:04:33.620Z","parentId":"215ba1de-9650-4a06-bda7-a80c9a0a0f18"}
